content.webTitle: Pick of the Week: Central: Clubs

fields.headline: Pick of the Week: Clubs
fields.bodyText: Godskitchen Air, Birmingham, Saturday 25 Apr Superstar DJ Carl Cox doesn't play many UK dates these days so expect a roadblock for this one-oﬀ at Air with a strong supporting lineup. Whoop! Godskitchen Syndicate, Bristol, Saturday 25 Apr The Call On Me-reworking king of Euro cheese trance plugs in for a session of electro housery. Storm 9th Birthday Emporium, Coalville, Saturday 25 Apr Most clubs count themselves lucky to make nine weeks – let alone nine years – so three parps on the horn of longevity to this trance, house and techno favourite. Sugarbeat Club Superﬂy, Leicester, Saturday 25 Apr Breakbeat, electro and techno session with a guest slot from Utah Saints – as in "U, U, U, U-tah Saints". And don't say you don't remember it. Zane Lowe Ramada Hotel, Kenilworth, Thursday 30 Apr Radio 1's breathlessly positive chief champion of new music plays box-fresh indie, rock and electro tuneage. Go the Zipper!
